---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="AdBunny — AI Banner Monetization for Remnant Inventory"
  description="Monetize remnant ad inventory with one JS tag. AdBunny's AI optimizes every banner impression in real time. No waterfall, no dev lift."
  keywords="remnant inventory monetization, banner ad monetization platform, AI ad optimization, programmatic banner ads, unsold ad inventory, single tag ad monetization"
>

<section class="min-h-screen pt-32 pb-20 max-md:pt-20 max-md:pb-14 relative overflow-hidden flex flex-col justify-center">
  <video src="/hero-video.mp4" autoplay loop muted playsinline class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover pointer-events-none" style="opacity:0.7;z-index:0"></video>
  <div class="absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none" style="background:rgba(10,10,10,0.2);z-index:1"></div>
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8 relative" style="z-index:2">
    <div class="text-center max-w-[52rem] mx-auto mb-16">
      <h1 class="font-extrabold leading-[0.95] tracking-tight mb-6" style="font-size:clamp(3rem,7vw,5.5rem)">Turn unsold ad space<br>into <span style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">revenue</span></h1>
      <p class="text-lg max-w-[30rem] mx-auto mb-10 leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag. AI-driven optimization. Zero conflict with your existing ad stack.</p>
      <div class="flex items-center justify-center gap-4">
        <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
        <a href="/how-it-works" class="btn btn-ghost btn-lg">How it works &rarr;</a>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="max-w-[40rem] mx-auto">
      <div style="background:rgba(10,10,10,0.55);border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08);backdrop-filter:blur(12px);-webkit-backdrop-filter:blur(12px)">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.06)">
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15)"></span>
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15)"></span>
          <span class="w-2.5 h-2.5" style="background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15)"></span>
          <span class="ml-3 text-xs" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">adbunny.js</span>
        </div>
        <pre class="p-6 font-mono text-xs leading-relaxed overflow-x-auto" style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.6)"><code style="color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85)">&lt;script src="cdn.adbunny.in/adbunny.js"
  data-publisher="your-tag"
  data-target="#ad-slot"&gt;
&lt;/script&gt;</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-24 max-md:py-16" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.65rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">For Publishers</div>
        <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-3">Fill remnant slots without touching your demand stack</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag. Same-day setup. No conflict with existing demand partners. AdBunny acts as a secondary layer — serving only when your primary stack passes.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.65rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">For Ad Networks</div>
        <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-3">Aggregated remnant inventory, one integration</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Programmatic access to remnant banner inventory across the AdBunny network with real-time performance reporting.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="text-[0.65rem] font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">AI Optimization</div>
        <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.5rem,3vw,2.25rem)] font-bold leading-snug tracking-tight mb-3">The best-paying ad, every single impression</h2>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Our AI evaluates demand per impression in real time, so every banner is the one most likely to pay best right now.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-24 max-md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-[1fr_1fr] gap-20 items-start max-md:grid-cols-1 max-md:gap-12">
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3.5rem)] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-tight mb-6">fill rate improved from<br><span style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">~35% to 89%</span></h2>
        <ul class="flex flex-col gap-3 mb-8">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)"><span class="split-check"></span> No conflict with existing demand</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)"><span class="split-check"></span> Same-day setup, no dev sprint</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-3 text-sm" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)"><span class="split-check"></span> AI optimizes every impression in real time</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="/publishers" class="split-link">learn more &rarr;</a>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div style="background:var(--color-surface);border:1px solid var(--color-border)">
          <div class="px-5 py-3" style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
            <span class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Fill Rate Improvement</span>
          </div>
          <div class="p-5 flex flex-col gap-2.5">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="w-7 text-[0.7rem] text-right shrink-0" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Mon</span><div class="h-7 flex items-center justify-end px-2.5 split-bar--accent" style="width:87%"><span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold">87%</span></div></div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="w-7 text-[0.7rem] text-right shrink-0" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Tue</span><div class="h-7 flex items-center justify-end px-2.5 split-bar--accent" style="width:91%"><span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold">91%</span></div></div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="w-7 text-[0.7rem] text-right shrink-0" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Wed</span><div class="h-7 flex items-center justify-end px-2.5 split-bar--accent" style="width:89%"><span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold">89%</span></div></div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="w-7 text-[0.7rem] text-right shrink-0" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Thu</span><div class="h-7 flex items-center justify-end px-2.5 split-bar--accent" style="width:93%"><span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold">93%</span></div></div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3"><span class="w-7 text-[0.7rem] text-right shrink-0" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Fri</span><div class="h-7 flex items-center justify-end px-2.5 split-bar--accent" style="width:88%"><span class="text-[0.7rem] font-semibold">88%</span></div></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="dark-noise py-24 max-md:py-16" style="background:var(--color-surface)">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8" style="position:relative;z-index:2">
    <div class="max-w-[32rem] mb-12">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(2rem,4vw,3rem)] font-bold leading-[1.1] tracking-tight">the proof writes itself</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-3 gap-12 max-md:grid-cols-1">
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">"AdBunny integrated in minutes and our remnant fill rate went from ~30% to over 85% within the first week."</p>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Sarah Chen</div>
        <div class="text-xs" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Head of Ad Ops, PublisherCo</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">"We were skeptical about another ad tag, but AdBunny's AI optimization genuinely outperformed our existing waterfall."</p>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Marcus Rivera</div>
        <div class="text-xs" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">Director of Monetization, AdNet+</div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">"The single-tag integration meant our engineering team didn't need to do anything. It just worked."</p>
        <div class="text-sm font-semibold">Priya Patel</div>
        <div class="text-xs" style="color:var(--color-text-tertiary)">VP Product, BannerFlow</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-24 max-md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-[80rem] mx-auto px-8 text-center">
    <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.75rem,3vw,2.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight mb-4">stop leaving remnant revenue on the table</h2>
    <p class="text-base max-w-[28rem] mx-auto mb-8" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">One tag. AI-driven optimization. Revenue from inventory that used to sit empty.</p>
    <a href="/" class="btn btn-primary btn-lg">Get Your JS Tag</a>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="py-24 max-md:py-16">
  <div class="max-w-[44rem] mx-auto px-8">
    <div class="mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-[clamp(1.5rem,2.5vw,2rem)] font-bold tracking-tight">FAQs</h2>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left bg-transparent border-none py-5 text-[0.9375rem] font-semibold cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4" style="color:var(--color-text)">Will AdBunny conflict with my existing ad stack?</button>
        <div class="faq-a overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease" style="max-height:0"><div class="pb-5 text-[0.9375rem] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">No. AdBunny is built to run on remnant inventory only, so it fills what your primary demand doesn't reach. There's no conflict because AdBunny acts as a secondary layer — it only serves ads when your primary stack passes on an impression.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left bg-transparent border-none py-5 text-[0.9375rem] font-semibold cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4" style="color:var(--color-text)">How long does setup take?</button>
        <div class="faq-a overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease" style="max-height:0"><div class="pb-5 text-[0.9375rem] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Typically minutes. It's one JS tag — not a waterfall, not an SDK integration, not a server-side change. Paste the tag into your pages or ad slots and you're live.</div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="border-bottom:1px solid var(--color-border)">
        <button class="faq-q w-full text-left bg-transparent border-none py-5 text-[0.9375rem] font-semibold cursor-pointer flex justify-between items-center gap-4" style="color:var(--color-text)">What kind of fill rates can I expect?</button>
        <div class="faq-a overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease" style="max-height:0"><div class="pb-5 text-[0.9375rem] leading-relaxed" style="color:var(--color-text-secondary)">Our network average is ~89% fill rate on remnant inventory, compared to ~35% with traditional static waterfalls. Results vary by traffic and inventory, but most publishers see an immediate uplift.</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>
